        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Keulan,</P><P>I did not get mine till I was in my mid-50's.  It really depends on your playstyle.</P><P>The groups, soloing and raids I did, I did not know I needed it.</P><P>Then one time in Hate, during a wipeout.  The Pre-nerf CoS would have saved us lots of time.</P><P>And there was the time running through Kael where invis broke halfway through.  I did get out alive, cause my Jboots were clicked, but a close call sucks and could have easily been a lengthy CR.</P><P>Now that we have SoS that lasts a specific amount of time, then you should not have invis break when you do not want it to break when running through areas.</P><P>But, the CoS is an incredible piece for your bag of tricks and you should have one if you can get one.  Just like you should have essence emeralds and stalking probes (or Hog beads).</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157918" target=new>Ishtarra Gemeinseele </a><BR>Warlock of the Dirty Soul<BR>Uber N00b Extraordinaire<BR>Tunare Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
